<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-362-138  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 362 138.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  June 19 1989 v10 n25 p15(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Ameritrust aims for vendor independence. (Ameritrust Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Dooley, Bill.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Ameritrust Corp, known as a leader in the use of informationtechnology to improve customer service, is planning a $10 millionenhancement to its information system operation.andP;  The goals are tobecome vendor-independent and to emphasize an open systemsarchitecture to enable any branch bank of any size to incorporateapplications.andP;  Ameritrust also wants to be able to adapt andintegrate technology as it becomes available.andP;  The bank willincorporate DEC's MicroVAX 2000 series into its existing tellerequipment.andP;  Ameritrust operates IBM mainframes and a cluster ofDEC VAX 6310s for branches at the home site.andP;  The bank's branchesare tied together by Ethernet and IBM's SNA is used to connectbranches to the host.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   AmeriTrust Corp. (management).andO;Ticker:    AMTR.andO;Topic:     Information SystemsTechnologyBankingVendor Relations.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>